<p>I have one table with varchar2 datatypes like below</p>  <pre><code>create table t11 (aa varchar2(100),bb varchar2(100)); </code></pre>  <p>Now, if I trying to insert <code>systimestamp</code> into above, values are getting inserted:</p>  <pre><code>insert into t11 values (systimestamp,systimestamp); commit; </code></pre>  <p>Question is why this conversion is allowed in Oracle.</p>  <p>I am using Oracle 11g.</p>